      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/31/5",
      "text": [
        ": «صَلِّ لَيْلَةَ إِحْدَى وَ عِشْرِينَ وَ ثَلاَثٍ وَ عِشْرِينَ مِائَةَ رَكْعَةٍ تَقْرَأُ فِي كُلِّ رَكْعَةٍ اَلْحَمْدَ مَرَّةً وَ «قُلْ هُوَ اَللّٰهُ أَحَدٌ» عَشْرَ مَرَّاتٍ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2019 - Sulayman Al-Ja’fari narrated from Abu Al-Hasan (as) that he said:\n\"Pray on the nights of the 21st and 23rd (of Month of Ramadan) 100 units (rak’ahs), reciting Al-Hamd (Surah Al-Fatihah) once and Qul Huwa Allahu Ahad (Surah Al-Ikhlas) ten times in each unit.\""
        ]
      }
    },
